# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LLM PROVIDER — run the council on your Claude sub OR your ChatGPT/Codex sub.
# No API key, no per-call billing: it drives the local CLI you're already
# logged into. Pick ONE.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# claude (default) | codex
LLM_PROVIDER=claude

# --- If LLM_PROVIDER=claude --------------------------------------------------
# Uses the Claude Agent SDK against your Claude Code login. Just be logged in:
#   claude            # then /login   (or run: claude setup-token)
# Make sure ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is NOT set, or the SDK bills the API instead of
# your subscription. Optional model overrides (defaults: sonnet / opus):
# CLAUDE_EXPERT_MODEL=sonnet
# CLAUDE_SYNTH_MODEL=opus

# --- If LLM_PROVIDER=codex ----------------------------------------------------
# Uses the Codex SDK against your ChatGPT plan. Log in once:
#   codex             # then "Sign in with ChatGPT"   (or: codex login)
# Make sure OPENAI_API_KEY / CODEX_API_KEY are NOT set, or Codex bills the API
# instead of your ChatGPT subscription. Optional overrides:
# CODEX_EXPERT_MODEL=gpt-5-codex
# CODEX_SYNTH_MODEL=gpt-5-codex
# CODEX_REASONING_EFFORT=medium    # minimal | low | medium | high | xhigh

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UPSHOT API (optional)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Override the Upshot API base URL
# UPSHOT_API_BASE=https://api-mainnet.upshotcards.net/api/v1

# Dollars per 1 SHOT. Upshot exposes no SHOT/USD rate, so set this to let the
# council compute USD expected-value directly; otherwise it reports the
# break-even SHOT price instead of guessing a rate.
# UPSHOT_SHOT_USD=0.00195

# --- Bunny Shield bypass (optional, for server-side card fetch) ---
# Upshot's API sits behind Bunny Shield, which flags IPs. To let the server
# fetch cards directly (instead of pasting JSON), replay your browser session:
# open the card in your logged-in browser → devtools → Network → any
# api-mainnet request → copy these two headers.
#
# Bearer token (Authorization value, with or without the "Bearer " prefix):
# UPSHOT_BEARER=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
#
# Cookie header — this is what actually clears the shield; include the
# bunny_shield / bunny_shield_chk cookies. Short-lived & IP-bound.
# UPSHOT_COOKIE=bunny_shield=...; bunny_shield_chk=...
